                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <locus target="#173vb">f. 173vb</locus>
                           <desc>: Donation note.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           
                           <note> Short version of Additio 1, written in the same hand. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a5">
                           <locus target="#173rb">f. 173rb</locus>
                           <desc>: Record concerning the foundation of the church.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez"> ዛቲ፡ ታቦት፡ ዘተትክለት፡ በዘመነ፡ ማርቆስ፡
                              እምድኅረ፡ ነግሠ፡ ንጉሥነ፡ ኢዮአስ፡ በ፮ዓመት፡ ዘተከለቶ፡ &lt;...&gt;</q>
                           
                           <note> The tabot (church) of Bet Muḫaʿ Mikāʾel was established during the
                              6th year of the reign of King ʾIyoas (=1761 A.D.). The name of the
                              person who set it up was washed out. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1"><desc>- <locus target="#17r">17r</locus>, 18r: Titles of the
                           chapters written in the upper margins.</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e2"><desc> Names of the donor and some
                           of his relatives written in the upper margins (i.e. <locus target="#17r">17r</locus>, 18r).</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e3"><desc>  <locus target="#1v">1v</locus>: pen trial
                           (?).</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e4"><desc> <locus target="#59rb">59rb</locus>: supplication
                           formula.</desc></item>
